snippet: Officials in California have begun to set up an online marketplace where millions of residents will be able to shop for medical coverage.
abstract: California, home to seven million uninsured people, is at the forefront of preparations for a controversial component of the new health care law that will soon require most Americans to have medical coverage or pay a penalty; state officials have begun to set up an online marketplace where millions of residents will be able to shop for medical coverage.
lead_paragraph: Officials in California have begun to set up an online marketplace where millions of residents will be able to shop for medical coverage.
